      <h2>Introduction<a href="#instructions">&darr;</a></h2>
      <h4>Byakko was created to track manga. It remembers the manga you want to read and notifies you when a new chapter has been released. With each release, you can either read it on another online reader or on byakko, or you can download it as a cbz comic file.
	<br>
	Byakko was not created to replace great online readers such as Batoto. Know that while Byakko does allow you to read manga online, it is not an archive service-it only provides subscribed manga chapters. To read high quality scans of old already-released manga, I would suggest you head over to Batoto.
	<br>
	Byakko was only created to track manga releases. In the end, I want to create a service that scanlators are happy with. Most scanlators hate websites such as Mangafox, and I hope to earn a better reputation. This means that I do not earn ANY money of off this site. Though donations are welcome, they will always be forwarded to making Byakko better (i.e server costs). Though it will take time, I also hope to allow scanlators to supply Byakko with custom info such as manga download URLs, delay requests, URLs for online reading etc.
	<br>
	Byakko is also currently free of charge. This should not change without good reason.
      </h4>
