      <h2><a style="font-size:1.3em;" href="#menunav">&uarr;</a><a href="#futureplans">&uarr;</a>Behind the Scenes</h2>
      <h4>Byakko is my first real project written for the web. It is written in Ruby on Rails and is hosted on Heroku. It currently uses the heroku postgresql database to store user and manga information. It runs on one web dyno with no Amazon S3 CDN caching. It uses unicorn and newrelic. I have a separate heroku application which processes new releases every 6 hours. All new releases are downloaded and stored in a google doc for multiple downloads. Byakko recieves information of new chapters from mangaeden's API and downloads the chapters from them as well. 
	<br>
	<br>
	The source code is available on <a style="text-decoration:underline" href="https://github.com/projectdelphai/byakko">Github</a> for those who want to look at it.
